cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper focuses on privacy-enhancing techniques to mitigate sensitive information disclosure in deep learning inference pipelines. It discusses potential information exposure and formulates the problem as a reconstruction privacy attack. Therefore, it is highly likely to belong to this category.
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper deals with deep learning systems and their deployment as backend engines of AI services. It proposes a system to partition deep learning models and protect the confidentiality and integrity of user inputs. Hence, it is also likely to belong to this category.
3. cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper proposes a privacy-enhancing system for deep learning inference pipelines. It discusses security breaches, exploited vulnerabilities, neglect, or insiders that might lead to accidental disclosures of sensitive user data. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to this category.
4. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper leverages secure enclave techniques on cloud infrastructures to cryptographically protect the confidentiality and integrity of user inputs. Hence, it is also likely to belong to this category.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a system to partition deep learning models and protect the confidentiality and integrity of user inputs. It discusses performance overhead and provides a comprehensive security analysis and performance measurement. Therefore, it is also likely to belong to this category.
